  • java.lang.Object
    • popt4jlib.MSSC1D.Params

  • public class Params
extends java.lang.Object
    auxiliary class that implements a container to hold the MSSC1D problem inputs and various auxiliary data-structures.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Params

        public Params(double[] arr,
              double p,
              int m)
        3-argument public constructor. Distance metric to be used is the L1 norm.
        Parameters:
        arr - double[] the sequence to be clustered. Doesn't have to be sorted in ascending order, and is not modified in any way.
        p - double the maximum value for the sum of intra-distances of points from their center for any cluster. May be Double.MAX_VALUE to indicate no constraint.
        m - int the number of clusters required.

      • Params

        public Params(double[] arr,
              double p,
              int k,
              int metric)
        4-argument public constructor, is like the 3-arg constructor, but also specifies in its last argument, the distance metric to be used.
        Parameters:
        arr - double[] the sequence to be clustered. Doesn't have to be sorted in ascending order, and is not modified in any way.
        p - double the maximum value for the sum of intra-distances of points from their center for any cluster. May be Double.MAX_VALUE to indicate no constraint.
        k - int the number of clusters required.
        metric - int 0 indicates the L1-norm (Manhattan distance), 1 indicates the L2-norm (Euclidean distance).

      • Params

        public Params(cern.colt.matrix.DoubleMatrix1D arr,
              double p,
              int m)
        3-argument public constructor for COLT 1D arrays. Distance metric is set to the L1 norm.
        Parameters:
        arr - DoubleMatrix1D
        p - double as in double[]-based 3-argument constructor.
        m - int as in double[]-based 3-argument constructor.
